## F → Purchasing Habits
**Top 3 Decision Triggers:**
1. Hitting a plateau in their net worth growth and feeling frustrated by a flat market month.
2. A stressful week at work that makes them desperately crave an exit strategy.
3. Seeing a data-backed, logical breakdown of how a new system outperforms their current strategy.

**Prior Purchases For This Pain:**
1. Robo-advisor accounts (Betterment, Wealthfront)
2. Premium subscriptions to financial news (Wall Street Journal, Seeking Alpha)
3. Small, experimental deposits into crypto exchanges (Coinbase) or trading apps (Robinhood) where they tried to trade manually and failed or got bored.

**Price Tolerance For Offer:**
High. They easily spend $100/month on software subscriptions, gym memberships, and coffee. They understand the concept of "ROI" (Return on Investment). If a tool costs $100/month or takes a 4% performance cut, but mathematically yields an 18% monthly return, they will happily pay it because the net profit justifies the expense.

**Time Horizon Of Solution:**
Medium-Short. They want to see proof of concept within the first 30 to 60 days. They are patient enough not to expect overnight millions, but they need to see the software actively making profitable trades within the first month to trust the system.

