## H → Empathy Map
**Seeing:**
They are seeing their peers brag about massive gains on social media. They are seeing housing prices skyrocket out of reach. They are seeing their Vanguard portfolio move at a snail's pace, barely beating inflation.

**Thinking:**
"I work too hard to feel this financially insecure. There has to be a better way to compound my wealth without turning into a full-time day trader. I know the hedge funds use algorithms; why can't I?"

**Hearing:**
They are hearing financial influencers tell them to "just keep buying the S&P 500." They are hearing their parents tell them to buy a house and settle down. They are hearing the constant hum of economic anxiety in the news.

**Feeling:**
Trapped, tired, and deeply analytical. They feel a low-grade, constant stress about their financial trajectory, mixed with a strong desire to find a logical, technological "hack" to fix it.

**Saying:**
"I don't have the time to learn technical analysis, but I'm tired of settling for 8% a year." "I'd gladly pay for a service if it actually delivered alpha." "Robo-advisors are a joke."

**Doing:**
Scrolling Reddit finance threads late at night. Transferring money into a standard brokerage account but feeling uninspired by the options. Working long hours and trying to optimize their savings rate, but knowing you can't "save" your way to massive wealth.
